'''Harriet Baber''' (born January 6, 1950<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/34057770|title=The World who's who of women.|date=1995|publisher=International Biographical Centre|isbn=9780948875120|edition=13th|location=Cambridge, England|oclc=34057770}}</ref>) is a professor of Philosophy at the [[University of San Diego]]. She holds a Ph.D from [[Johns Hopkins University]], 1980. Her research interests are in analytic [[metaphysics]], [[philosophical theology]], [[feminism]] and [[philosophy of economics]]. In addition, Baber writes for ''[[The Guardian]]'' (UK) and is a regular columnist for ''[[Church Times]]'' (UK).<ref>http://www.linkedin.com/pub/harriet-baber/a/56/b18</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.sandiego.edu/~baber/|title=H. E. Baber|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sandiego.edu/cas/phil/faculty/biography.php?ID=199|title=Faculty and Staff - Department of Philosophy - College of Arts and Sciences - University of San Diego|publisher=}}</ref> She is an [[Episcopal Church (United States)|Episcopalian]].
