'''Ingrid A.M. Robeyns''' (born 1972) holds the Chair Ethics of Institutions at Utrecht University, Faculty of Humanities and the associated Ethics Institute.<ref>http://www.ingridrobeyns.nl/</ref>

Robeyns is also a Fellow of the [[Human Development and Capability Association]] (HDCA) and was elected the associations eighth president in April 2017.<ref name=Fellows>{{cite web|title=HDCA Fellows|url=https://hd-ca.org/about/hdca-fellows|publisher=Human Development & Capability Association|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Robeyns is from [[Leuven]] in Belgium. She gained a Belgium [[Licentiate (degree)|licentiate]] qualification in economics from the [[Katholieke Universiteit Leuven]] (''the Catholic University of Leuven'') in 1994. She went on to study social and political science in Germany at the [[University of Göttingen|Georg August Universität, Göttingen]] (''University of Göttingen''). Robeyns returned to the Katholieke Universiteit Leuven for her [[Master of Science|MSc]] in economics which she completed in 1997.

Her [[Doctor of Philosophy|doctorate]] in philosophy and economics came from the [[University of Cambridge]] in 2003, her dissertation was on gender inequality and the capacity approach.<ref name=Morris>{{Citation | last = Morris | first = Christopher | contribution = Contributors | editor-last = Morris | editor-first = Christopher | title = Amartya Sen | pages = xii – xiii | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge New York | year = 2009 | isbn = 9780521618069 }}</ref> Robeyns also has an [[Master of Arts|MA]] in philosophy from the [[Open University]] (2007).<ref name=Morris /><ref name=Born>{{cite web|last=Robeyns|first=Ingrid|title=CV| url= http://www.ingridrobeyns.nl/CV/index.html|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>

== Academic career ==
In 2006 the [[Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research]] (NWO) awarded her a five-year Vidi grant for research on theories of justice.<ref name=Morris /> The research considers what the question of justice means within the welfare state for children, parents and non-parents.<ref name=VIDI>{{cite web|title=Social justice and the new welfare state|url=http://www.eur.nl/fw/onderzoek/programma/constitution_normative_practices/vidi_socialjustice/|publisher=Eramus University Rotterdam|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>

== Personal ==
Robeyns claimed dual Dutch / Belgium citizenship in 2013.<ref name=Citizen>{{cite web|last=Robeyns|first=Ingrid|title=One woman, two votes|url=http://crookedtimber.org/2013/10/13/one-woman-two-votes/|publisher=Crooked Timber|accessdate=17 April 2014|date=13 October 2013}}</ref>

