[[File:Mr-yoga-scales-pose.jpg|alt=scales-pose|thumb|scales-pose - hand position variation]]
'''Tulasana''' ({{lang-sa|तुलासन}}; [[IAST]]: ''Tulāsana''), '''Balance Pose''',<ref name="Kumar">{{cite book|last=Kumar|first=Brijesh|title=Enhance Your Sexual Potency|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YfjV2vqqM4wC&pg=PA40|accessdate=1 July 2011|publisher=Diamond Pocket Books (P) Ltd.|isbn=978-81-288-0540-0|pages=40–}}</ref> '''Dolasana''' ('''Swing Pose'''),<ref name="Joshi2005">{{cite book|last=Joshi|first=K S|title=Yoga In Daily Life|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PsGxfYRYdFMC&pg=PA116|accessdate=1 July 2011|date=1 March 2005|publisher=Orient Paperbacks|isbn=978-81-222-0049-2|page=116}}</ref> '''Tolasana''' ('''Scale Pose'''),<ref name="Swenson2001">{{cite book|last=Swenson|first=Doug|title=Power Yoga for Dummies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z4VnORiAs8kC&pg=PT281|accessdate=1 July 2011|date=1 June 2001|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|isbn=978-0-7645-5342-4|page=281}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.yogajournal.com/poses/1706 | title = Yoga Journal - Scale Pose | accessdate = 2011-07-01}}</ref> or '''Utthita Padmasana''' ('''Raised Lotus Pose''')<ref name="Mahatyagi2007">{{cite book|last=Mahatyagi|first=Raman Das|title=Yatan Yoga: A Natural Guide to Health and Harmony|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IjpmZ3ysHTsC|accessdate=1 July 2011|date=14 November 2007|publisher=YATAN Ayurvedics|isbn=978-0-9803761-0-4|pages=166–7}}</ref> is an [[asana]].

==Etymology==
The name comes from the Sanskrit words ''tula'' (तुला) meaning "balance",<ref name="Goel">{{cite book|last=Goel|first=Satish|title=Sex For All|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tJoi3Awl-qwC&pg=PA69|accessdate=1 July 2011|publisher=Diamond Pocket Books (P) Ltd.|isbn=978-81-7182-029-0|page=69}}</ref> and ''asana'' (आसन, āsana) meaning "posture" or "seat".<ref name="Sinha1996">{{cite book|last=Sinha|first=S.C.|title=Dictionary of Philosophy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-zzRvh1fRzEC&pg=PA18|accessdate=9 April 2011|date=1 June 1996|publisher=Anmol Publications PVT. LTD.|isbn=978-81-7041-293-9|page=18}}</ref>

==Description==
From [[Lotus position|Padmasana]] the practitioner with the hands placed either side of the hips raises the entire torso, legs, and feet using the arms and shoulders.

==Benefits==
The asana strengthens the back, shoulders, and hips.<ref name="Majumdar1968">{{cite book|author=Sachindra Kumar Majumdar|title=Yoga for physical and mental fitness|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x8rWAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=1 July 2011|date=June 1968|publisher=Stravon Educational Press|page=54|quote=This exercise strengthens the back, shoulders, and hips. }}</ref>

==Contraindications and cautions==
The asana should not be practiced with current or recent shoulder or wrist injuries.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://yoga.isport.com/yoga-guides/how-to-do-scale-pose-in-yoga | title = How to Do Scale Pose in Yoga | accessdate = 2011-07-01 | publisher = iSport.com}}</ref>

